kathirasen.name: A. Kathirasen
kathirasen.bio: A. Kathirasen has spent 45 years in journalism typing under the illusion that people actually read his writings.

draj.name: D. Raj
draj.bio: The writer is a forgetful person. But then, if you are telling the truth, you donâ€™t have to remember everything.

dennisignatius.name: Dennis Ignatius
dennisignatius.bio: Dennis Ignatius is a former ambassador.

imran.name: Imran Ariff
imran.bio: Imran believes that Malaysia's youth are under represented in the national discourse. This is his attempt to change that (hopefully without justifying it)

parkaran.name: K. Parkaran
parkaran.bio: K. Parkaran remains an eternal optimist believing that we will see a Bangsa Malaysia one day.

murallitharan.name: M. Murallitharan
murallitharan.bio: Dr M. Murallitharan is a public health physician and leads various medical professional and civil society organisations. He is actively engaged in health system reforms especially in dealing with non-communicable diseases.

mariam.name: Mariam Mokhtar
mariam.bio: Mariam Mokhtar is a fierce critic of the socio-political problems of Malaysia, who wishes to rid the country of extremism, intolerance and double-standards.

sharifah-munirah-alatas.name: S. Munirah Alatas
sharifah-munirah-alatas.bio: S. Munirah Alatas is a social science scholar who, after retirement, has become more insightful about academic inertia, mediocrity and political interference in higher education institutions.

tajuddin.name: Tajuddin Rasdi
tajuddin.bio: Prof Tajuddin Rasdi seorang ilmuwan seni bina Islam dan pengulas veteran isu pendidikan, politik, Islam serta bina bangsa.

wanharon.name: Wan Haron Wan Hassan
wanharon.bio: Wan Haron Wan Hassan is a senior practising corporate lawyer with more than 20 years of experience, and is active in civil society movements working towards a better and safer Malaysia.

yeoh-guan-jin.name: Yeoh Guan Jin
yeoh-guan-jin.bio: Yeoh Guan Jin shares his perspective on matters that matter to some of us.
